In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt. Drain peaches, reserving syrup. Add syrup and rhubarb to saucepan; mix well. Bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes. Add peaches and vanilla. Pour into an ungreased 2-1/2-qt. baking dish; set aside. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in yogurt and vanilla just until combined. Drop by tablespoons onto hot fruit. Bake, uncovered, at 400 degrees F for 30 minutes. Serve warm.